ng their personal orientations to English and self-perceptions as English learner-users. It also examines individuals’ responses to these factors and discusses fluctuations in their motivations. The additional value of this book lies in its detailed account of methodological procedures, challenges and ways to overcome obstacles encountered when undertaking qualitative longitudinal studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEmotive (Linguistics)zJapan. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxJapanese speakers. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxJapanese students. 0aEthnicityzJapan. 0aSecond language acquisitionzJapan. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aEmotions.  aEnglish language education in Japan.  aEnglish learners' self perception.  aIdentity.  aL2 ideal self.  aLanguage learning.  aNarrative studies.1 aMiyahara, Masuko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060670640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178309382340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781783093823423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781783093823/original  a978-3-11-060670-6  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK